item.title: China Rules Out Animal Market and Lab as Coronavirus Origin
item.description: Chinese scientists in recent days said they had ruled out both a laboratory and an animal market in the city of Wuhan as possible origins of the coronavirus pandemic, in their most detailed pushback to date against allegations from U.S. officials and others over what might have sparked it.

item.title: China's Military Chief in Hong Kong Vows to Protect Beijing's Interests
item.description: The head of China’s military garrison in Hong Kong said his soldiers would safeguard the country’s national security interests in the city, reinforcing an aggressive push by the Communist Party to tighten its grip on the former British colony.

item.title: Boris Johnson's Defense of Aide Meets Mounting Calls for Dismissal
item.description: Prime Minister Boris Johnson’s efforts to defend top aide Dominic Cummings struggled as an opinion poll showed a majority of the British public believed the adviser had broken lockdown rules and more lawmakers called for his dismissal.

item.title: Russia Sends Warplanes to Libya, Escalating Its Involvement, U.S. Says
item.description: Senior U.S. military officials said Russia has sent jet fighters to Libya to support Russian mercenaries fighting there on behalf of Khalifa Haftar, a militia leader based in the eastern part of the country.

item.title: Mexico's Economy Shrinks in First Quarter on Early Pandemic Effects
item.description: Mexico’s economy contracted 1.2% in the first quarter of the year, as the coronavirus pandemic started to affect industry and services. The decline was smaller than the preliminary 1.6% contraction reported at the end of April.

item.title: Western Economies See Biggest Slump Since Financial Crisis
item.description: The world’s developed economies saw the largest fall in output since the global financial crisis in the first three months of the year, as governments began to impose lockdowns designed to limit the spread of the novel coronavirus.

item.title: Coronavirus Further Strains a U.K. Union Already Under Pressure
item.description: England, Scotland, Wales and Northern Ireland, still reeling from Brexit, go their separate ways in trying to manage the pandemic.
